---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
import SectionHeading from '../components/SectionHeading.astro';
import CTABanner from '../components/CTABanner.astro';
import ClientLogos from '../components/ClientLogos.astro';
import { SUITES } from '../lib/constants';
---

<PageLayout
  title="1404 — AI Agents for Business Operations"
  description="AI agent teams that handle executive operations, financial intelligence, business development, acquisitions, and exit preparation. Purpose-built for your business, connected to your systems, managed by us."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <Hero />

  <!-- What We Build -->
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-24 md:py-32">
    <SectionHeading title="What we build" />

    <div class="space-y-6 text-text-body text-base leading-relaxed mb-16">
      <p>
        We build agent teams — groups of specialized AI workers that take over specific operational functions in your company. You tell us what's eating your time. We build a team of agents trained on your business, connect them to your existing systems, and manage them on an ongoing basis.
      </p>
      <p>
        Each agent team handles a different function. Some handle the daily executive workload — email triage, morning reports, meeting prep. Others handle financial analysis, or business development, or acquisition research. They run continuously and get better over time because they're learning your business as they work. We offer two ways to work with us.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Two Tiers -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-16">

      <!-- Agent Suites -->
      <div class="border border-border rounded-sm p-8 bg-bg-card">
        <p class="font-mono text-xs text-copper mb-4 tracking-wide">AGENT SUITES</p>
        <h3 class="font-display text-2xl text-text-primary mb-4">Pick the function you need handled</h3>
        <p class="text-text-body text-base leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Each suite is a team of agents built for a specific operational function. Start with the one that solves your biggest problem. Add more when you're ready.
        </p>
        <a href="/agents" class="text-sm text-copper hover:text-copper-bright transition-colors duration-200">
          See all suites &rarr;
        </a>
      </div>

      <!-- Partnership -->
      <div class="border border-copper-dim rounded-sm p-8 bg-bg-card">
        <p class="font-mono text-xs text-copper mb-4 tracking-wide">PARTNERSHIP</p>
        <h3 class="font-display text-2xl text-text-primary mb-4">The full technology department</h3>
        <p class="text-text-body text-base leading-relaxed mb-6">
          CTO leadership, custom engineering, every agent suite, and a research function that monitors what's coming in your industry. For companies that want a full technology department without building one internally.
        </p>
        <a href="/partnership" class="text-sm text-copper hover:text-copper-bright transition-colors duration-200">
          Learn more &rarr;
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Suites -->
  <section class="border-t border-border">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-24 md:py-32">
      <SectionHeading
        title="Agent Suites"
        subtitle="Each suite is a team of specialized agents trained on your business and connected to your systems."
      />

      <div class="space-y-10">
        {SUITES.map((suite) => (
          <a href={`/agents/${suite.slug}`} class="block group">
            <div class="border border-border-light rounded-sm p-8 bg-bg-card hover:border-copper-dim transition-colors duration-200">
              <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start md:justify-between gap-4 mb-4">
                <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-text-primary group-hover:text-copper transition-colors duration-200">
                  {suite.name}
                </h3>
                <p class="text-xs text-text-muted font-mono shrink-0">
                  Replaces: {suite.replaces}
                </p>
              </div>
              <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">
                {suite.short}
              </p>
            </div>
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why This Works -->
  <section class="border-t border-border">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-24 md:py-32">
      <SectionHeading title="Why this works" />

      <div class="space-y-6 text-text-body text-base leading-relaxed mb-16">
        <p>
          Most companies have tried some version of AI at this point. They've used ChatGPT, maybe experimented with a copilot tool. The results are usually the same — interesting but not operational. It answers questions, but it doesn't do work.
        </p>
        <p>
          The difference is in how an agent is built. A language model on its own can answer questions, but it can't do anything about the answers — it has no access to your email, financials, CRM, or project tools. What makes an agent operational is connecting it to those systems and then training it on how your business actually works. That's what we do — we build purpose-built teams that know your business and handle work from start to finish.
        </p>
      </div>

      <a href="/how-it-works" class="text-sm text-copper hover:text-copper-bright transition-colors duration-200">
        See exactly how it works &rarr;
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Trust -->
  <section class="border-t border-border">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-24 md:py-32">
      <SectionHeading title="Built for enterprise" />

      <p class="text-text-body text-base leading-relaxed mb-12">
        We operate inside your infrastructure — financials, email, project data. That level of access requires security and compliance infrastructure that most firms our size don't build until much later. We started early because the companies we want to work with run due diligence before granting that kind of access.
      </p>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4 mb-10">
        <div class="border border-border-light rounded-sm px-5 py-4 bg-bg-card">
          <p class="font-mono text-xs text-copper mb-1 tracking-wide">SOC 2 Type II</p>
          <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm">In progress — Q3 2026</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-border-light rounded-sm px-5 py-4 bg-bg-card">
          <p class="font-mono text-xs text-copper mb-1 tracking-wide">Security Policies</p>
          <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm">14 policies written</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-border-light rounded-sm px-5 py-4 bg-bg-card">
          <p class="font-mono text-xs text-copper mb-1 tracking-wide">AI Governance</p>
          <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm">NIST AI RMF aligned</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-border-light rounded-sm px-5 py-4 bg-bg-card">
          <p class="font-mono text-xs text-copper mb-1 tracking-wide">Client Isolation</p>
          <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm">Dedicated infrastructure per client</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <a href="/trust" class="text-sm text-copper hover:text-copper-bright transition-colors duration-200">
        Full security and compliance details &rarr;
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Backed by TCG -->
  <section class="border-t border-border">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-24 md:py-32">
      <SectionHeading title="Backed by The Construct Group" />

      <div class="space-y-6 text-text-body text-base leading-relaxed mb-12">
        <p>
          1404 was built inside a real operating company. The Construct Group — a national retail fixture installation company — was our first client and became an equity partner after we built their entire technology department from scratch. We built them a 180,000-line unified operations platform, deployed AI agent teams to run daily executive operations, and provide ongoing CTO leadership.
        </p>
        <p>
          TCG continues to operate on our platform and agent infrastructure, and their CEO actively refers other operators to 1404 — which is how most of our clients find us. The agent architecture, security model, and delivery process were all built and validated in production with TCG before we took a second client.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-8 mb-12">
        <div>
          <p class="font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl text-copper mb-2">12</p>
          <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm">Integrated modules</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl text-copper mb-2">125x</p>
          <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm">Faster forecasting</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl text-copper mb-2">75 hrs</p>
          <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm">Saved per week</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl text-copper mb-2">98%</p>
          <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm">Inventory accuracy</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <a href="/case-studies/tcg" class="text-sm text-copper hover:text-copper-bright transition-colors duration-200">
        Read the full case study &rarr;
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Client Logos -->
  <ClientLogos />

  <!-- CTA -->
  <CTABanner />
</PageLayout>
